   "source": [
    "# Linear BMM with full Bayesian calibration of coleman toy models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "careful-kitchen",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The models can be found in Coleman Thesis : https://go.exlibris.link/3fVZCfhl\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook shows how to use the Bayesian model mixing package **Taweret** for a toy problem. \n",
    "\n",
    "Author : Dan Liyanage \n",
    "\n",
    "Date : 19/21/2022"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "nasty-shift",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Steps for linear BMM\n",
    "    1. Get Models with a prediction method\n",
    "    2. Choose a Mixing method \n",
    "    3. Estimate the mixture weights (parameters in the mixture function) with user defined calibration method\n",
    "To execute each step in this notebook we need to import the following from Taweret."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "emotional-foundation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, os.path.abspath('../../../../Taweret'))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "applied-special",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import models with a predict method\n",
    "from Taweret.models import coleman_models as toy_models\n",
    "# Mixing object with a likelihood method\n",
    "from Taweret.mix.linear import linear_mix as LM\n",
    "# Wrapper for the likelihood to be used with Bilby\n",
    "from Taweret.calibrate.likelihood_wrappers import likelihood_wrapper_for_bilby "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "residential-married",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# For plotting\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# For calibration\n",
    "import bilby\n",
    "\n",
    "# For other operations\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import shutil"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "generous-confidentiality",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "m1 = toy_models.coleman_model_1()\n",
    "m2 = toy_models.coleman_model_2()\n",
    "truth = toy_models.coleman_truth()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "stainless-stations",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "g = np.linspace(-1,9,10)\n",
    "plot_g = np.linspace(-1,9,100)\n",
    "true_output = truth.predict(plot_g)\n",
    "exp_data = truth.predict(g)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "prime-following",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 1. The models and the experimental data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "mexican-pipeline",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Truth\n",
    " \n",
    "$f(x) = 2-0.1(x-4)^2$, where $x \\in [-1, 9]$\n",
    "\n",
    "Model 1\n",
    "\n",
    "$f_1(x,\\theta)= 0.5(x+\\theta)-2$    , where $\\theta \\in [1, 6]$\n",
    "\n",
    "Model 2\n",
    "\n",
    "$f_2(x,\\theta)= -0.5(x-\\theta) + 3.7$   , where $\\theta \\in [-2, 3]$\n",
    "\n",
    "Experimental data \n",
    "\n",
    "sampled from the Truth with a fixed standard deviation of 0.3\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "expired-dryer",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1440x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sns.set_context('notebook')\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(20,5))\n",
    "prior_ranges = [(1,6), (-2,3)]\n",
    "for i in range(0,2):\n",
    "    ax = axs.flatten()[i]\n",
    "    ax.plot(plot_g, true_output[0], label='truth', color='black')\n",
    "    ax.errorbar(g,exp_data[0],exp_data[1], fmt='o', label='experimental data', color='r')\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim(-2,4)\n",
    "    for value in np.linspace(*prior_ranges[i],10):\n",
    "        if i==0:\n",
    "            predict_1 = m1.predict(plot_g, value)\n",
    "            ax.plot(plot_g, predict_1[0])\n",
    "            ax.set_ylabel(r'$f_1(x)$')\n",
    "        if i==1:\n",
    "            predict_2 = m2.predict(plot_g, value)\n",
    "            ax.plot(plot_g, predict_2[0])      \n",
    "            ax.set_ylabel(r'$f_2(x)$')    \n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('x') \n",
    "    \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "hydraulic-resident",

    "pos_predictions = np.array(pos_predictions).reshape(-1,len(plot_g))"
